<header class="guide-header">
  <h1>Content Creators</h1>
  <p class="guide-series">Privacy Resources</p>
</header>

<p class="resource-intro">Follow these content creators to learn about privacy.</p>

<div class="resource-list">

<h3 class="resource-subheading">YouTube</h3>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@TheHatedOne" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Hated One</a></h3>
  <p>One of the best YouTube content creators when it comes to privacy, digital politics and institutional critique of digital power.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@NaomiBrockwellTV" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NBTV</a></h3>
  <p>A great channel from a non-profit that offers engaging and easy to understand guides and analysis videos about privacy and security.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@MentalOutlaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mental Outlaw</a></h3>
  <p>A comedic tech YouTuber who focuses mainly on privacy, cybersecurity and digital rights news.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@TheLinuxEXP" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Linux Experiment</a></h3>
  <p>A great channel that offers news, guides and insights into the Linux operating system.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@EricMurphyxyz" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Eric Murphy</a></h3>
  <p>A great channel with many key insights into privacy.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@rossmanngroup" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Louis Rossman</a></h3>
  <p>A man who wakes up every morning fighting Big Tech. Mainly focuses on the right to repair but does occasionally cover privacy and security related matters.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@simoncaine9515" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Simon Caine</a></h3>
  <p>A smaller channel that covers privacy news.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@techlore" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Techlore</a></h3>
  <p>One of the big ones when it comes to privacy on YouTube.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@JackRhysider" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Jack Rhysider</a></h3>
  <p>Channel of the Darknet Diaries Podcast.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@sideofburritos" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Side of Burritos</a></h3>
  <p>Channel that mainly offers GrapheneOS guides.</p>
</div>

<h3 class="resource-subheading">Podcasts</h3>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://darknetdiaries.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Darknet Diaries</a></h3>
  <p>A podcast about hackers, breaches, shadow government activity, hacktivism, cybercrime, and all the things that dwell on the hidden parts of the network.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.surveillancereport.tech/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Surveillance Report from Techlore</a></h3>
  <p>Weekly security and privacy news.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://closednetwork.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Closed Network Privacy Podcast</a></h3>
  <p>A privacy and security podcast focused on the everyday person and using simple tools and techniques to become a smaller target for online attacks.</p>
</div>

<div class="resource-item">
  <h3><a href="https://www.eff.org/how-to-fix-the-internet-podcast" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">EFF &ndash; How to Fix the Internet</a></h3>
  <p>EFF's How to Fix the Internet podcast offers a better way forward. Through curious conversations with some of the leading minds in law and technology, it explores creative solutions to some of today's biggest tech challenges.</p>
</div>

</div>
